\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch\ltrch\hich\loch{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }}{{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0 [45]\tab Contrary to the view held by the Commission, Mrs Alegra testified that barriers to entry in the glaze market were high because the manufacture of glaze required technical skills and good design as well as economies of scale to achieve a level of prof
itability.  In her evidence, she further stated that while the price of glaze was important, the success of glaze producers was dependent to a large extent on whether they were able to compete on all three levels for high volume customers.  }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj\tx6045{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [46]    Ferro\'92s poor record in the glaze market demonstrated that if a glaze manufacturer could not compete on quality, design and service levels it would not be able to compete for large volume business despite its low prices.    Furthermore, it seems tha
t a glaze producer would not be able to achieve any considerable presence in the market without being able to secure large volume business from tile manufacturers, who were the largest consumers of glaze.  Mr Forbes himself conceded that Ferro did not have
 the necessary expertise to become successful in the glaze market in the short term and that Ferro\'92s initial forecasts of achieving 20% market share in approximately two years had to be modified once they experienced the realities of the market. Mr Gonzalv
es of Smalticeram also testified that it was not easy to enter the glaze market successfully without obtaining a supply contract with a large customer.  Glaze production also required specialized skills which were particularly scarce in South Africa.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [47]\tab Accordingly we conclude that barriers to entry in the glaze market are relatively high and require specialized skills, technical know-how as well as experience in the broader ceramics design industry.  Glaze manufacturers also require large volume cus
tomers in order to achieve economies of scale.  On the evidence presented to us, it would take considerably longer than 24 months for a new entrant to be able to effectively compete with the merged entity or Spectrum.  }
